==English==

===Etymology===
From [[hydro-]] "water" + [[plane]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈhaɪdrəʊˌpleɪn/}} (''[[RP]]'')
*{{IPA|/ˈhaɪdroʊˌpleɪn/}} (''US'')
*{{audio|en-us-hydroplane.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|hydroplane|hydroplanes|hydroplaned|hydroplaning}}

#To [[skim]] the surface of a body of [[water]] while moving at high [[speed]].
#:''Don't drive too fast on wet roads or the car may '''hydroplane''' and cause you to loose control of the vehicle.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun|hydroplane|hydroplanes}}

#{{nautical}}: A specific type of [[motorboat]] used exclusively for [[racing]].
# A [[hydrofoil]]
# A [[seaplane]]
# The wing of a [[submarine]], used to help control depth.

